The paper deals with the problem of hybrid analog and digital precoding for downlink mmWave massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed scheme also involves optimization and iterative procedures, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY). The use of mmWave frequencies and massive MIMO also relates to multimedia (cs.MM) and augmented reality (cs.AR) applications.
